    "fr": "Then be watchful about the time of daily prayers. Do not offer them before time because you are free, nor delay them because you are busy. For someone asked the Prophet, peace be upon him and his progeny, about the timings, and the Prophet replied: Jibreel came to me and showed me the timings. He prayed Zuhr when the sun passed the meridian as it declined to his right, then he showed me Asr when the shadows became equal to object size. Then he prayed Maghrib when the sun set, and Isha when the twilight disappeared, and Subh in the last part of the night's darkness near dawn as the stars flickered. So pray on these times, and remain constant on the known tradition and the clear path.",
    "de": "Then be watchful about the time of daily prayers. Do not offer them before time because you are free, nor delay them because you are busy. For someone asked the Prophet, peace be upon him and his progeny, about the timings, and the Prophet replied: Jibreel came to me and showed me the timings. He prayed Zuhr when the sun passed the meridian as it declined to his right, then he showed me Asr when the shadows became equal to object size. Then he prayed Maghrib when the sun set, and Isha when the twilight disappeared, and Subh in the last part of the night's darkness near dawn as the stars flickered. So pray on these times, and remain constant on the known tradition and the clear path.",
    "ru": "Then be watchful about the time of daily prayers. Do not offer them before time because you are free, nor delay them because you are busy. For someone asked the Prophet, peace be upon him and his progeny, about the timings, and the Prophet replied: Jibreel came to me and showed me the timings. He prayed Zuhr when the sun passed the meridian as it declined to his right, then he showed me Asr when the shadows became equal to object size. Then he prayed Maghrib when the sun set, and Isha when the twilight disappeared, and Subh in the last part of the night's darkness near dawn as the stars flickered. So pray on these times, and remain constant on the known tradition and the clear path.",
    "zh": "Then be watchful about the time of daily prayers. Do not offer them before time because you are free, nor delay them because you are busy. For someone asked the Prophet, peace be upon him and his progeny, about the timings, and the Prophet replied: Jibreel came to me and showed me the timings. He prayed Zuhr when the sun passed the meridian as it declined to his right, then he showed me Asr when the shadows became equal to object size. Then he prayed Maghrib when the sun set, and Isha when the twilight disappeared, and Subh in the last part of the night's darkness near dawn as the stars flickered. So pray on these times, and remain constant on the known tradition and the clear path."
